From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 10:37:18 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: ti: iot2050: Disable UHS modes on sdhci1

Systems equipped with the EC20 modem may fail to boot from SD card due
to instability on the shared 1.8V signaling rail used for MMC UHS
operation.

Disable 1.8V signaling on sdhci1 to prevent the controller from
switching to UHS modes.

While this limits the maximum SD card transfer rate, the impact on
IOT2050 workloads is negligible compared with the benefit of improved
boot reliability.

Signed-off-by: Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common-pg2.dtsi | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common-pg2.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common-pg2.dtsi
index b3c4c0eec3dc..149bc29ef356 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common-pg2.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/ti/k3-am65-iot2050-common-pg2.dtsi
@@ -1,10 +1,11 @@
 // SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
 /*
- * Copyright (c) Siemens AG, 2021-2023
+ * Copyright (c) Siemens AG, 2021-2026
  *
  * Authors:
  *   Chao Zeng <chao.zeng@siemens.com>
  *   Jan Kiszka <jan.kiszka@siemens.com>
+ *   Li Hua Qian <huaqian.li@siemens.com>
  *
  * Common bits of the IOT2050 Basic and Advanced variants, PG2
  */
@@ -33,3 +34,7 @@ &dss {
 	/* Workaround needed to get DP clock of 154Mhz */
 	assigned-clocks = <&k3_clks 67 0>;
 };
+
+&sdhci1 {
+	no-1-8-v;
+};
